Description: Ostracon, fragment of the wide-rim of a buff-coloured pottery shallow dish, the fabric contains a number of small white inclusions, the whole was originally covered with a red-orange slip, the ledge-rim is incised with three lines of Coptic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393860) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393860)
